column5: As others have said, really great that you were able to capture that. Thanks for showing it.  You do know that it's illegal to use walleye for bait eh?
Crazy video, haha too cool. Nice walleye btw
Really Cool.  She wasn't gonna give up that meal.
Really Cool Simon,1rst thought was,just like Swamp People,was waiting for Troy to shout "soot soot"

Well Simon,  I knew you are kind and polite gentleman but this was taking it too far my friend  Asking so politely that musky so many times to give your fish back was a like a text book example of a polite Canadian behaviour ha ha ha  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
Awesome simon thanks for sharing
Neat video never had a Musky try & steal my stringer just a big snapping turtle.....

Great video and the musky was just so calm the whole time ! A very "don't mind me while I grab some lunch off your stringer' kind of attitude lol. I couldn't quite tell however, but did the musky finally let go or did it swallow the walleye whole ?
Very cool.  Makes you think twice about relieving yourself off the side of the boat too!!

Thanks for the replies      I thought that was only illegal on a Thursday afternoon. Jeeze...they really make the regs so complicated!    I just gave the stringer a gentle shake and it eventually let go.
Cool video!  Can't believe he wouldn't let it go.
Just another reason not use a stringer, eh........(only on fly in trips do I use a stringer)  Nice video BTW......
Very cool Simon ................... so did you Waypoint that spot?
that was awesome-thanks for sharing..I've only ever had a snapper go after a stringer
That's a huge fish, great video.
absolutely...its between a rock and a hard place!

Don't think there's much out there that would spook a musky...  :-)  I once caught a pike the same way when I was a kid.  It attacked our stringer and I just yanked the whole thing out of the water.  He soon occupied the spot right next to his would-be meal.  Both were delicious.

LOL...poetic justice.   I have this little clip from the same bay a week ago.....Pike vs Pike.   The fish were hungry there this week.      <iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/YBRl6dsP2rQ" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
That's a great video man.  One to remember!

There is some great footage of this happening under a kayak on youtube......look up anglersthree I believe...they make some great vids.  Great that you got the footage and posted though....goes down nicely with my coffee this morning
really cool video thanks for posting
Thought someone strung up a musky for the table haha.  Pretty neat..

Had a musky bite into my stringer today. Would love to show the video...lol.    OK DARN IT....HERE IT IS!    MUSKY ON A STRINGER VIDEO  <iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/PSEJVea_3xI" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
Theres a small lake near here that has Walleye. Lots of stories of stringers being attacked over the side of the boat. Yep musky.  Pm the vid if you like Simon.
I would love to see that vid as well
why cant you show it Simon? Would love to see it...not like you were fishing for it...
Are you sure   Might be a Dryden secret.
I think we'd all like to see it.   Matt.
You need to clip a big 7/0 treble on the end of that stringer Simon
Had that happen here...  Broke a clip right of my stringer...
POST THE DARN VID SIMON.GET IT OVER WIT.
Simon, just tell the truth, you were fishing OOS musky and using those 'eyes on your stringer as bait!  LOL!!!
HEHEHE LMAO.
I agree lets see the video.
If you follow Simons, You tube,you will see it.
Oh goody.......
That was pretty cool!
That was cool Simon, I saw it on your youtube page.  You should post it, awesome
awesome video simon
that was great! could have picked him up out of the water I bet
That was wild !!! He almost appeared to be a tamed fish.Was spooked by you at all.
That's awesome, thanks for posting! Glad to see you kept the walleye too lol.
cool vid and +1 subs
So cool! Thats happened to almost everyone at some point, supper friggin cool you captured it!!!!!

That was awesome Simon, thanks for sharing! Probably a good decision not trying to pick it up. He was lethargic with a fish in his mouth but something tells me he would have gone nuts having his dinner(or your dinner lol) taken away and being picked up! Could have hurt either one of you!  -Ben
Very cool.I'm the same way with my dinner.Won't let go of it either.
